   argument count check (the `!argc` part of the original condition) should be
   removed, or the condition should be `if (argc > 0 && !be_tobool(vm, 1))`.
   This makes `assert()` always pass. If `assert()` is indeed expected to always
   be provided an argument, then the error should be a "wrong argument count"
   error, not an "assert failed" error, which implies an assert condition failed
   (not that the syntax/call was wrong).

